<item>
            <title>[OAK-409] OSGi related dependencies should be set to provided scoped and not marked as optional</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-409</link>
                <project id="12313221" key="OAK">Jackrabbit Oak</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently the OSGi related dependencies org.osgi.core and org.osgi.compendium are marked as optional. Due to this packages under org.osgi.* are marked as optional which is not correct. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As such dependencies are already marked as provided scope they would not be included as part of transient dependencies. For more details refer to &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Fix: The optional flag should be removed&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;http://markmail.org/thread/njukyten6fdipts3&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://markmail.org/thread/njukyten6fdipts3&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12613758">OAK-409</key>
